Run Instructions:
1) Rest Service
	- Run the spring boot project. Class - com.lloyds.clock.HumanFriendlyClock.HumanFriendlyClockApplication
	- Sample URL - https://localhost:8080/clock/?time=01:30 or https://localhost:8080/clock/ (tested using postman)
	- Test cases for the Rest API have been added.
	
2) Command Line Program:
	- Command Line program can be using shell script -  humanFriendlyClock.sh
	- Steps to run - 
		- Extract HumanFriendlyCommandLine.zip, contents of the file
			- slf4j-api-1.7.3.jar and HumanFriendlyClock.jar for the class path
			- humanFriendlyClock.sh - to run the application from command line
			- command to run 
				- ./humanFriendlyClock.sh
				- ./humanFriendlyClock.sh 18:30